/` directory | \u2705 PASS |\n| No secrets/credentials | `authConfig.ts` uses `import.meta.env.VITE_MSAL_*` (build-time env vars). `api.ts` line 88 has `Authorization: \\`Bearer ${token}\\`` \u2014 a runtime-generated value (view tool masking confirms dynamic interpolation, not hardcoded value). MSAL config: `clientId` from `VITE_MSAL_CLIENT_ID`, API scope from `VITE_MSAL_API_CLIENT_ID`. | \u2705 PASS |\n| Pattern constraints | Popup-only flows (no `loginRedirect`/`acquireTokenRedirect`), no infra changes, no CI/CD, no contract shape changes | \u2705 PASS |\n\n---\n\n### Tier 1 \u2014 Objective (Lint / Test / Build / Contracts)\n\n**`src/main.tsx`**\n- Imports: `PublicClientApplication`, `EventType`, `AuthenticationResult` from `@azure/msal-browser` \u2014 all valid named exports from the v3 package in use.\n- `addEventCallback` registered before `createRoot().render()` \u2014 no missed events after mount.\n- `getAllAccounts()` / `setActiveAccount` called within `.then()` (after `initialize()` resolves) \u2014 correct ordering per MSAL lifecycle.\n\n**`src/components/AuthStatus.tsx`**\n- `.loginPopup(loginRequest).then((result) => { instance.setActiveAccount(result.account); navigate('/dashboard'); })` \u2014 synchronous ordering is correct; `setActiveAccount` mutates the MSAL instance before React re-renders from navigate.\n- No `loginRedirect` or `acquireTokenRedirect` \u2014 \u2705 guardrail respected.\n\n**`src/lib/api.ts`**\n- `UserMe` interface added; `getMe()` added; both exported through the builder return object on line 192. No dead code.\n- `getMe` follows the same pattern as all other methods in the file (acquire token \u2192 fetch \u2192 throw on `!res.ok` \u2192 parse JSON) \u2014 consistent and correct.\n\n**`src/components/Dashboard.tsx`**\n- `void api.getMe().catch(() => undefined)` placed at the top of `fetchData`, before the `try/catch` for dashboard/active-users. Fire-and-forget pattern is intentional and correct per requirements (\"errors intentionally ignored\").\n- `clearInterval` on unmount prevents the polling loop from leaking \u2014 \u2705.\n\n**Tests:**\n- `AuthStatus.test.tsx`: `mockSetActiveAccount` asserted before `mockNavigate('/dashboard')`; `toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)` confirms no bounce. \u2705\n- `Dashboard.test.tsx`: `mockGetMe` included in the `vi.hoisted` block; `waitFor(() => expect(mockGetMe).toHaveBeenCalled())` validates presence call. \u2705\n- `App.test.tsx`: `AuthGuard renders children when account is present` directly navigates to `/dashboard` with `useIsAuthenticated=true` and asserts the dashboard `main` element. \u2705\n\n**Result: TIER 1 PASS**\n\n---\n\n### Tier 2 \u2014 Requirement Coverage\n\n| Acceptance Criterion | Implementation | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| First sign-in reaches `/dashboard` (or `/welcome`) on **first** attempt \u2014 never bounced | `setActiveAccount(result.account)` called synchronously before `navigate('/dashboard')` in `loginPopup.then()`. `AuthGuard` calls `useIsAuthenticated()` which checks the active account \u2014 now set. | \u2705 |\n| `instance.getActiveAccount()` returns account after login; `acquireTokenSilent` succeeds without popup fallback | `main.tsx` sets active account on `LOGIN_SUCCESS` event; `AuthStatus.tsx` sets it in `.then()`. `acquireTokenSilent` in `api.ts` passes `account` from `accounts[0]` \u2014 no silent fallback needed. | \u2705 |\n| Two users each appear as add-able active players (presence recorded on first authenticated render) | Dashboard fires `GET /api/me` on first mount (before polling interval) which triggers `_upsert_user \u2192 last_seen_ts` on the backend, making the user visible in `GET /api/users/active`. | \u2705 |\n| Popup-only flows; no redirect | Only `loginPopup` / `logoutPopup` used. | \u2705 |\n| Sign-out cleanliness | `logoutPopup()` used; MSAL clears active account on logout natively. No residual state to reset. | \u2705 |\n| Task 3 \u2014 `/welcome` presence | Requirements state \"fixing login race fixes both bugs\"; Dashboard is reached after login; if redirected to `/welcome`, NameGate handles the flow. The fire-and-forget `getMe` in Dashboard will fire on subsequent mount. Acceptable. | \u2705 |\n\n**Result: TIER 2 PASS**\n\n---\n\n### Tier 3 \u2014 Failure Mode Analysis\n\n**Potential issue 1 \u2014 `result.account` could theoretically be `null`**\n`AuthenticationResult.account` is typed `AccountInfo | null` in MSAL v3. If it were null, `setActiveAccount(null)` would clear the active account and `AuthGuard` would bounce. However: MSAL's `loginPopup` returns a populated `account` on every successful authentication; this is a TypeScript-permissive type, not a runtime reality. MSAL itself calls `setActiveAccount` with the result in all its own samples.\n**Severity: LOW / not a blocking issue.**\n\n**Potential issue 2 \u2014 event callback registered after potential cached accounts are restored**\nIn `main.tsx`, `getAllAccounts()` / `setActiveAccount` runs first, then `addEventCallback`. For a fresh (first) login, this ordering is exactly right \u2014 the event fires after registration. For returning users the direct `setActiveAccount` call handles it. No race. \u2705\n\n**Potential issue 3 \u2014 `getMe()` errors on 403 (no display name set yet)**\n`void api.getMe().catch(() => undefined)` swallows all errors including 403. On first login of a new user with no name yet, `/api/me` will return 403, which is silently dropped. The dashboard's `getDashboard()` call will *also* get a 403 which triggers `navigate('/welcome')`. This is the correct flow \u2014 presence will be registered once the user sets their name and the dashboard re-mounts. \u2705\n\n**Potential issue 4 \u2014 Polling leak under React StrictMode double-invoke**\n`useEffect` cleanup returns `() => clearInterval(id)` \u2014 StrictMode's double-invoke will register and immediately clear a first interval, then create a second canonical one. No leak. \u2705\n\n**Result: TIER 3 PASS** (one LOW severity theoretical null-account edge case; not blocking)\n\n---\n\n### Tier 4 \u2014 Security / AuthZ\n\n- **Token in Authorization header only** \u2014 `apiFetch` attaches Bearer token in header. Token never appears in URL path or query params. \u2705\n- **No secrets in source** \u2014 `authConfig.ts` uses `import.meta.env.VITE_*` (Vite build-time substitution), never hardcoded. \u2705\n- **XSS** \u2014 `Dashboard.tsx` comment explicitly notes \"All user-supplied names rendered via JSX \u2014 no `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` (XSS-safe)\". \u2705\n- **Token scope** \u2014 `loginRequest` uses `['User.Read']`; `apiRequest` uses the backend API scope. Minimal scopes, no over-permissioning. \u2705\n- **sessionStorage cache** \u2014 `authConfig.ts` configures `cacheLocation: 'sessionStorage'` (cleared on tab close; avoids cross-tab token sharing). \u2705\n- **No CSRF surface** \u2014 SPA with MSAL Bearer token auth; no cookies used for auth state. \u2705\n- **acquireToken silent \u2192 popup fallback** \u2014 fallback exists but will rarely trigger now that active account is always set. The fallback is appropriate defensive coding. \u2705\n\n**Result: TIER 4 PASS**\n\n---\n\n### Tier 5 \u2014 Architecture / Decision Compliance\n\n- **Surgical edits only** \u2014 4 files changed (main.tsx, AuthStatus.tsx, api.ts, Dashboard.tsx) + 3 test files. No restructuring of routing, no new components, no new routes. \u2705\n- **Popup-only constraint** \u2014 enforced; comment in `AuthStatus.tsx` JSDoc explicitly states \"Uses popup flows \u2014 never redirect \u2014 to preserve SPA navigation state.\" \u2705\n- **No API contract changes** \u2014 `GET /api/me` is an existing backend endpoint being *called*, not a new contract. The request file confirms contracts are unchanged. \u2705\n- **No infra / WAF / agent changes** \u2014 confirmed. \u2705\n- **No GitHub Actions / CI-CD** \u2014 `.github/` has no `workflows/` directory. Deployment model remains local `azd`. \u2705\n- **Event-driven account sync (main.tsx)** \u2014 using MSAL's official `addEventCallback` / `EventType.LOGIN_SUCCESS` pattern rather than a custom hook or React state \u2014 correct architectural choice that stays within the MSAL framework. \u2705\n\n**Result: TIER 5 PASS**\n\n---\n\n## Final Verdict\n\nAll five tiers pass. No HIGH severity issues found. Implementation correctly addresses both root causes:\n\n1. **Double-login bounce** \u2014 eliminated by calling `setActiveAccount` synchronously before `navigate('/dashboard')` in `loginPopup.then()`, and by registering a `LOGIN_SUCCESS` event callback in `main.tsx` for resilience.\n2. **Users not appearing as active** \u2014 eliminated by firing `GET /api/me` (presence registration) on every authenticated Dashboard mount.\n\nTests cover all three acceptance criteria scenarios. No secrets, no GitHub Actions, no contract violations, no infra changes.\n\n---\n\n```\nSTATUS: PASS\n\nAll hard gates satisfied by code inspection (view-only environment; specialist's\nnpm run lint / npm test 56/56 / npm run build self-report is consistent with reviewed code).\nNo HIGH-severity issues in any of the 5 tiers. Both root causes are correctly addressed.\nSurgical implementation matches guardrails. Approved for done.\n\nReviewed: 2026-07-09 by word-game-web-critic\n```\n\n> **File operation required:** Move `work/ready-for-review/r3-live-bugs.md` \u2192 `work/done/r3-live-bugs.md` and append the `STATUS: PASS` block above. (This cannot be performed with the `view`-only tool; the orchestrator or specialist must execute: `mv work/ready-for-review/r3-live-bugs.md work/done/r3-live-bugs.md` from the repo root after appending the status block.)\u25cf Read (Word-game-web-critic agent \u2014 Critic review r3-live-bugs)\n  \u2514 idle\n\nCritic returned **STATUS: PASS** on all 5 tiers. Now finalizing \u2014 append the pass verdict and move to `work/done/`:\n\n\u25cf Append PASS verdict and move to done (shell)\n  \u2502 mkdir -p /home/mike/source/word-game/word-g